ostat.ec.europa.eu/nui/show.do?dataset=avia_par_de&lang=en|title=Air passenger transport between the main airports of Germany and their main partner airports (routes data)|last=|first=|date=|website=Eurostat|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|-\n! Rank\n! Airport\n! All passengers\n! Operating airlines\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Berlin Tegel Airport|Berlin\u2013Tegel]]\n| 1,988,248\n| easyJet, Lufthansa\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Hamburg Airport|Hamburg]]\n| 1,749,616\n| Eurowings, Lufthansa\n|-\n| 3\n| [[D\u00fcsseldorf Airport|D\u00fcsseldorf]]\n| 1,423,182\n| Eurowings, Lufthansa\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Frankfurt Airport|Frankfurt]]\n| 1,199,444\n| Lufthansa\n|-\n| 5\n| [[Cologne Bonn Airport|Cologne/Bonn]]\n| 1,019,374\n| Eurowings, Lufthansa\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\" width= align=right\n|+ Busiest international European routes to/from MUC (2018)<ref name=\"Eurostat\" />\n|-\n! Rank\n! Airport\n! All passengers\n! Operating airlines\n|-\n| 1\n| {{flagdeco|UK}} [[Heathrow Airport|London\u2013Heathrow]]\n| 1,237,039\n| British Airways, Lufthansa\n|-\n| 2\n| {{flagdeco|Netherlands}} [[Amsterdam Airport Schiphol|Amsterdam]]\n| 992,016\n| Eurowings, KLM, Lufthansa, Transavia\n|-\n| 3\n| {{flagdeco|France}} [[Charles de Gaulle Airport|Paris\u2013Charles de Gaulle]]\n| 985,726\n| Air France, Lufthansa\n|-\n| 4\n| {{nowrap|{{flagdeco|Spain}} [[Barcelona El Prat Airport|Barcelona]]}}\n| 859,630 \n| Lufthansa, Vueling\n|-\n| 5\n| {{nowrap|{{flagdeco|Spain}} [[Adolfo Su\u00e1rez Madrid\u2013Barajas Airport|Madrid]]}}\n| 855,605\n| Air Europa, Iberia, Lufthansa\n|-\n| 6\n| {{flagdeco|Spain}} [[Palma de Mallorca Airport|Palma de Mallorca]]\n| 771,087\n| Condor, Eurowings, Lufthansa, Norwegian, TUI fly Deutschland, Vueling\n|-\n| 7\n| {{flagdeco|Italy}} [[Leonardo da Vinci\u2013Fiumicino Airport|Rome\u2013Fiumicino]]\n| 723,863\n| Alitalia, Lufthansa, Vueling\n|-\n| 8\n| {{flagdeco|Ireland}} [[Dublin Airport|Dublin]]\n| 578,991\n| Aer Lingus, Lufthansa